main event: One disc-shaped object about the size of a half dollar was observed for about 2 minutes. A bright white light was seen at the top, turning on and off, fading in and out.
interesting points: The object moved in a straight line and then made a very fast 180-degree turn.
The object was observed 10 degrees above the horizon in a westerly direction.
The sighting occurred at night, and the visibility was clear with unlimited range.
The witness was an unidentified individual from Winchester, California.
The report concluded that the cause of the sighting was undeterminable.
